com.freebase.json
Class JSON

java.lang.Object
  com.freebase.json.JSON
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.json.simple.JSONAware
public class JSON
extends Object
implements org.json.simple.JSONAware

This class is a telescopic (meaning, jQuery-like) wrapper for all the various classes that can make up a JSON object. While using JSON in Javascript or Python comes natural, dealing with it in Java is a pain, mostly because of casting issues. Having a single wrapper object that encapsulates all those casting issues allows us to cascade the method calls. So something that in javascript would be 

   var a = b.c[1].d[3];
can be translated in Java as: 
   String a = b.get("c").get(1).get("d").get(3).string();
which is a lot more verbose but still better than having to deal with all the casting between Map and List and String by hand.
